  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-CON-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. This package was signed at an earlier timestamp; one validation result and one supporting evidence item were appended post-signing without re-signing, introducing a future-dated evidence consistency flaw (W-CON-03). The narrative notes the package was 'updated post-signing' to incorporate late-arriving mesh refinement data, but no new signature was applied.",
