      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Mesh convergence and discretization error validation — centrifugal pump MRL5",
      "description": "Grid convergence index (GCI) study performed on three systematically refined meshes (6M, 18M, 54M elements) for the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry. Apparent order of convergence p=1.92; GCI_fine=2.7% for hemolysis index QoI. Richardson extrapolation applied. This result was appended to the package after the package signature was issued to incorporate the final 54M-element run, which completed on the HPC cluster after the submission deadline.",
      "evidenceTimestamp": "2025-11-14T09:22:00Z"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-cou2-experimental-comparison",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Experimental hemolysis index comparison — 5 operating points",
      "description": "CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against in-vitro measurements at 5 flow-speed combinations (2.5 L/min/2500 RPM through 6 L/min/3500 RPM). Mean absolute error 8.3%; all predictions within 15% of measured values. Monte Carlo UQ (n=2000 samples) performed over inlet velocity, blood viscosity, and power-law hemolysis model coefficients. 95th-percentile NIH remains below clinical threshold of 0.01 g/100 L.",
      "evidenceTimestamp": "2025-10-03T14:00:00Z"
    },
    {
